-- Brazil’s TIM Appeals Regulator’s Decision on New Phone Chips
-- B y   M a r i o   S e r g i o   L i m a
-- 2012-07-21T13:54:23Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-21/brazil-s-tim-appeals-regulator-s-decision-on-new-phone-chips.html
Tim Participacoes SA (TIMP3)  has appealed to
a federal court a decision by Brazil’s telecommunications
regulator, known as Anatel, which banned sales of new phone
chips in 18 states and Distrito Federal, the company said in an
e-mailed statement sent yesterday.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mario Sergio Lima in Brasilia Newsroom at 
 mlima11@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Sylvia Wier at   swier@bloomberg.net  